{"id":407443869,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"2 years, 10 months","timestamp":1602441563,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"1212 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/407443869/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Wildcard Matching","memory":"22.8 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def isMatch(self, s: str, p: str) -> bool:\n        ns, np = len(s), len(p)\n        dp = [[False for _ in range(np + 1)] for _ in range(ns + 1)]\n        dp[0][0] = True\n        if ns == 0 and np == 0:\n            return True\n        if np == 0:\n            return False\n        for j in range(1, np + 1):\n            if p[j-1] == \"*\":\n                dp[0][j] = dp[0][j-1]\n        \n        for i in range(1, ns + 1):\n            for j in range(1, np + 1):\n                # if match\n                if p[j-1] == \"?\" or s[i-1] == p[j-1]:\n                    dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1]\n                # if not match\n                if p[j-1] == \"*\":\n                    # case 1: empty sequence\n                    dp[i][j] = dp[i][j-1]\n                    # case 2: length >= 1\n                    dp[i][j] = dp[i][j] or dp[i-1][j]\n        return dp[-1][-1]","compare_result":"","title_slug":"wildcard-matching","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
